  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for xorg-x11-server",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for xorg-x11-server provides the following fixes:\n\n- CVE-2017-10971: Fix endianess handling of GenericEvent to prevent a stack overflow by clients. (bnc#1035283)\n- Make sure the type of all events to be sent by ProcXSendExtensionEvent are in the\n  allowed range.\n- CVE-2017-10972: Initialize the xEvent eventT with zeros to avoid information leakage.\n\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
